place.name: SYDERSTONE
place.gazetteerText: SYDERSTONE, a parish, with a village, in Docking district, Norfolk; 4 miles SE of Docking r. station. It has a post-office under Fakenham. Acres, 2,520. Real property, £2,710. Pop., 528. Houses, 110. The manor belonged once to the Robsarts, and belongs now to the Marquis of Cholmondeley. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £534.* Patron, the Marquis of Cholmondeley. The church is good; and there are Wesleyan and Primitive Methodist chapels, and a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
